Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Pour @cold salted water{300%ml} into a #medium pot{} with a tight-fitting lid.

Stir in the @rice{150%g} and bring to the boil.

Once boiling, lower the heat to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pot from the heat.

Keep covered for ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

While the rice cooks, zest and juice half the @lemon{1%half}. Cut the remaining lemon into thick wedges.

In a #small bowl{}, stir together the @mustard{1%sachet}, @mayo{2%sachets}, @lemon zest{} and ½ tsp lemon juice.

Season to taste with @sugar{to taste}, @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

In a separate #bowl{}, combine @breadcrumbs{1%pack} with ½ tbsp @oil{1%tbsp}.

Trim the tip of the @broccoli{1%head}. Cut head into small florets and stem into 2cm pieces.

Peel and grate the @garlic{2}(peeled and grated).

Halve, deseed and finely chop the @chilli{1}(halved, deseeded and finely chopped).

Pop the broccoli onto a lined #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with a glug of @oil{to taste}, toss together with the @salt{to taste}, @pepper{to taste}, garlic and chilli. Spread out in a single layer. Set the tray aside.

Pat the @salmon{200%g} dry with #kitchen paper{} then season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}. 

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw fish.

Arrange the fillets, skin-side down, on a separate lined baking tray or #oven dish{}.

Spread half the mayo over the tops of the salmon fillets.

Spoon equal amounts of the breadcrumb mix onto each fillet. Press down firmly with the back of the #spoon{} to ensure it sticks.

Place the broccoli on the middle shelf of the oven and roast until the edges are crispy and slightly charred, ~{10-15%minutes}.

Bake the salmon on the top shelf of the oven until the fish is cooked through and the breadcrumbs are golden, ~{10-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Salmon is cooked when opaque in the middle.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and stir through @butter{1%tbsp} until melted and well incorporated.

Divide your salmon, broccoli and rice between plates.

Serve with the remaining mustard mayo on the side for dipping.